The term fiscalis is literally translated these days as ''financial'' as in ''annus fiscalis'' or financial year.

The term orginates from the root word fisc, or more commonly the <ref>fiscus</ref>. The fiscus was typically an ancient woven basket used by tax collectors to gather monies and return them to the Governor or Emperor. In time, the term fiscus came to represent the treasury of the Emperor himself.

The modern term fiscal year is a derivation of the very same, fiscal being a transliteration from the french.